b'       Dear Students,    Link       International Graduate Course for Continuing Professional Development is offered for researchers and engineers from developing countries to provide the opportunity of advanced study, research and experience in engineering fields so that they can contribute to the industrial development of their home countries.  Nagaoka University of Technology will nominate 10 masterE2s students and 10 doctoral students for 2017 Japanese Government (Monbukagakusho) Scholarship out of successful candidates from this course who meet the conditions of nomination for the Japanese Government Scholarship.  All programs for this course are conducted in English.  Please note that the application deadline is on October 7, 2016.    Application Procedure and Details:        Mr. Arvind Sivamani  Liaison Officer (Outgoing Students)  International Relations  Office of International Relations l 2 nd Floor, IC & SR Building  Indian Institute of Technology Madras l Chennai  600 036 l INDIA  Tel: (91) 0442257 4928  Email: oir4@wmail.iitm.ac.in   Website:       '

